5d.title: Development phase unpredictable
5d.text: Several proposed problems in [2l advanced safety] are alleged to be difficult because they depend on some property of a mature [2c agent] that is allegedly hard to predict in advance at the time we are designing, teaching, or testing the agent.  We say that such properties are allegedly 'development phase unpredictable'.  For example, the [47 Unforeseen Maximums problem] arises when [2j we can't search a rich solution space as widely as an advanced agent], making it development-phase unpredictable which real-world strategy or outcome state will maximize some formal utility function.
